1 Section 1. Section 79-8,112, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 79-8,112 The purpose of the Nebraska Teacher Recruitment and
4 Retention Act is to provide financial incentives to recruit and retain
5 teachers and paraeducators in Nebraska classrooms.
6 Sec. 2. Section 79-8,113, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
7 amended to read:
8 79-8,113 For purposes of the Nebraska Teacher Recruitment and
9 Retention Act:
10 (1) Department means the State Department of Education;
11 (2) Grant means a grant for teacher recruitment and retention
12 payments under the Nebraska Teacher Recruitment and Retention Act; and
13 (3) Paraeducator means an individual who is employed by a school in
14 Nebraska to provide instructional support and noninstructional services
15 to students and teachers in schools but who is not required to hold a
16 certificate to teach; and
17 (4) (3) Teacher means a person who holds a valid certificate to
18 teach in Nebraska issued by the Commissioner of Education and is employed
19 in Nebraska for the instruction of students in elementary or high school
20 grades.
21 Sec. 3. Section 79-8,114, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
22 amended to read:
23 79-8,114 (1) A teacher or paraeducator is eligible to receive a
24 grant as prescribed in this section may apply to the department for a
25 grant. The department shall not prioritize a grant based upon the school
26 where the teacher or paraeducator is employed applicant teaches. The
27 department shall distribute all grants automatically to the school
28 district employing the eligible teacher or paraeducator. The school
29 district shall distribute such grant funds to the teacher or paraeducator
30 in accordance with this section.
31 (2) A teacher is eligible to receive apply for:
