13 (d)(i) A high-need retention grant of five thousand dollars if on or
14 after June 2, 2023, a teacher:
15 (A) Obtains an endorsement in special education, mathematics,
16 science, technology, or dual credit; and
17 (B)(I) For an application submitted prior to April 17, 2024, signs a
18 contract to complete a school year of full-time employment as a teacher
19 at a Nebraska school in school year 2024-25, 2025-26, or 2026-27; or
20 (II) For an application submitted on or after April 17, 2024, signs
21 a contract to complete a school year of full-time employment as a teacher
22 to teach in such endorsement area at a Nebraska school in school year
23 2024-25, 2025-26, or 2026-27.
24 (ii) A teacher shall only be eligible to receive one high-need
25 retention grant.
26 (3) A paraeducator is eligible to receive:
27 (a) A retention grant of one thousand dollars if such paraeducator
28 signs a contract to work as a paraeducator and works on average twenty-
29 eight hours or more per week during the school year in school year
30 2025-26 or 2026-27; and
31 (b) A retention grant in an amount proportional to the grant
