5 Sec. 4. Section 79-8,115, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
6 amended to read:
7 79-8,115 It is the intent of the Legislature to encourage individual
8 schools and school districts to adopt policies incentivizing teacher and
9 paraeducator recruitment and retention through policies similar to the
10 Nebraska Teacher Recruitment and Retention Act. Teachers and
11 paraeducators at schools not adopting a recruitment and retention policy
12 shall not be prohibited from receiving a grant under the Nebraska Teacher
13 Recruitment and Retention Act.
14 Sec. 5. Section 79-1021, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
15 amended to read:
16 79-1021 (1) The Education Future Fund is created. The fund shall be
17 administered by the department and shall consist of money transferred to
18 the fund by the Legislature. Transfers may be made from the Education
19 Future Fund to the Computer Science and Technology Education Fund at the
20 direction of the Legislature. Any money in the Education Future Fund
21 available for investment shall be invested by the state investment
22 officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska
23 State Funds Investment Act.
24 (2) The fund shall be used only for the following purposes, in order
25 of priority:
26 (a) To fully fund equalization aid under the Tax Equity and
27 Educational Opportunities Support Act;
28 (b) To fund reimbursements related to special education under
29 section 79-1142;
30 (c) To fund foundation aid under the Tax Equity and Educational
31 Opportunities Support Act;
-4-

